	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				+10 vs. magic by itself alone won't usually be noticeable to most people.  It's when you begin accumulating a lot of these types of items that it<BR>
begins to show.  My char at level 24 (buffed with endure magic by a cleric) has a magic resist of about 85 thanks to all the + vs magic items I have.  How<BR>
this manifests seems to be that I resist spells a lot more than I normally would.  <BR>
<BR>
It's sort of like any other stat.  If your agility is normally 80, adding one +3 agil ring isn't going to be that noticeable.  However, if you get enough<BR>
magic items and buffs to raise your agil to 120, you'd notice you get hit a LOT less often than before. It is all cumulative.<BR>
<BR>
Also, re: the mantle.  I've seen these generally go for about 50 - 60 plat on my server, though folks get as much as 80 on occasion, depending on the <BR>
location.  It's the booby drop of the Knight in the tower.  Tunic is the rare drop, and though its stats aren't incredibly better than the mantle, the tunic fetches a lot more I believe simply because it shows on your char and therefore is a status thing. <BR>
<BR>
A
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
